<subSubSection pageNumber="760" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="760">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="760">Note:</emphasis>
In accordance with Art. 23.8, Ex. 19 of the Code, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="filix-fragile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="760">P. filix-fragile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is to be treated as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="760">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1754" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fragile">P. fragile</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Proctor (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="760">Ferns Jamaica</emphasis>
: 410. 1985) erroneously believed 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Copeland’s">Copeland's</normalizedToken>
type (as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“1251.44”">&quot;1251.44&quot;</normalizedToken>
) to have been a post-1753 addition to the collection and designated a cited Plukenet plate as type in its place. However, the type carries both the epithet and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“44”">&quot;44&quot;</normalizedToken>
written by Linnaeus, along with an Amman label suggesting it was in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
possession long before 1753.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
